  "text": "Acute arterial occlusion by an embolism or in situ thrombosis is a dramatic event which produces severe ischemia of distal tissue. The warning signs are the 5 Ps: pallor, pain, pulselessness, paralysis and paresthesia. In such cases, emergent restoration of blood flow by surgery may be vital to prevent limb loss [CITATION_1] . Aneurysms and dilated forms of atherosclerosis can be both the cause of in situ thrombosis as well as the source of an embolism [CITATION_2] .",
